{"article_id":"P4nxSMgRZZMxQFOF","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON ( ) -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The U.S. Supreme Court on Monday dealt a setback to President Donald Trump ,","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"requiring his administration to maintain protections","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"he has sought to end for hundreds of thousands of immigrants","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"brought illegally into the United States as children .","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"The justices refused to hear the administration ' s appeal of a federal judge ' s Jan. 9 nationwide injunction","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"that halted Trump ' s move","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"to rescind a program","depth":12},{"id":8,"text":"that benefits immigrants","depth":14},{"id":9,"text":"known as \" Dreamers \"","depth":14},{"id":10,"text":"implemented in 2012 by his Democratic predecessor , Barack Obama .","depth":13},{"id":11,"text":"The protections were due to start phasing out in March under the Republican president ' s action ,","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"announced in September .","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"Under the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"( DACA )","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"program , roughly 700,000 young adult , mostly Hispanics , are protected from deportation","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"and given work permits for two-year periods ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"after which they must re-apply .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Congress so far has failed to pass legislation","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"to address the fate of the \" Dreamers , \"","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"including a potential path to citizenship .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"San Francisco-based U.S. District Judge William Alsup ruled last month","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that the government must continue to process renewals of existing DACA applications","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"while litigation over the legality of Trump ' s action is resolved ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"prompting the administration ' s unusual move","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"to bypass a federal appeals court","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"and take the matter directly to the Supreme Court .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"\" The DACA program","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"- which provides work permits and myriad government benefits to illegal immigrants en masse -","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"is clearly unlawful .","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"The district judge ' s decision","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"to unilaterally re-impose a program","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"that Congress had explicitly and repeatedly rejected","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"is a usurpation of legislative authority , \"","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"White House spokesman Raj Shah said .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"\" We look forward to having this case expeditiously heard by the appeals court and ,","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"if necessary ,","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"the Supreme Court ,","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"where we fully expect to prevail , \"","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Shah added .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"The administration argued","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"Obama exceeded his powers under the Constitution","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"when he bypassed Congress","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"and created DACA .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Alsup ruled","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"that the challengers ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"including the states of California , Maine , Maryland and Minnesota and Obama ' s former homeland security secretary Janet Napolitano ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"were likely to succeed in arguing","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"that the administration ' s decision","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"to end DACA","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"was arbitrary .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"In a brief order , the Supreme Court justices said","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"the appeal was \" denied without prejudice , \"","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"indicating","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"they will maintain an open mind on the underlying legal issue","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"still being considered by the San Francisco-based 9th U.S . Circuit Court of Appeals .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"The justices also said","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"they expect the lower court to \" proceed expeditiously","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"to decide this case . \"","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Trump ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"meeting with governors at the White House ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"took a swipe at the appeals court ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"which has ruled against him in other key cases ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"as well as the broader American judiciary .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"\" It ' s really sad","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"when every single case","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"filed against us","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"is in the 9th Circuit .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"We lose ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"we lose ,","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"we lose","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"and then we do fine in the Supreme Court , \"","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Trump added .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"\" But what does that tell you about our court system ?","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"It ' s a very , very sad thing . \"","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"California Attorney General Xavier Becerra , a Democrat , called the administration ' s bid","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"to bypass the 9th Circuit","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"\" unusual and unnecessary \"","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"and said","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"the DACA program is \" fully legal .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"\" For the sake of the Dreamers","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"who help make our economy and our state strong ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"the rescission of DACA should not be allowed to stand , \"","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"Becerra said .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"Immigration activists said","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"they were grateful","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"the Supreme Court gave current DACA recipients more time ,","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"but said","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"many young immigrants are still left unprotected .","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"\" We need a permanent solution now , \"","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"said Greisa Martinez , a DACA recipient","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"who works in Washington with the immigrants ' rights group United We Dream .","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"\" This back and forth on DACA and the legislative process has created a crisis in our community . \"","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"The DACA dispute is the latest major case","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"brought to the Supreme Court for its consideration","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"arising from Trump ' s immigration policies .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"The justices are due to hear arguments in April on the legality of his latest travel ban order","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"barring entry to people from several Muslim-majority nations .","depth":6},{"id":98,"text":"Trump ' s move","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"to rescind DACA","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"prompted legal challenges by Democratic state attorneys general and various organizations and individuals in multiple federal courts .","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"On Feb. 13 , a second U.S. judge issued a similar injunction","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"ordering the administration to keep DACA in place .","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"U.S. District Judge Nicholas Garaufis in Brooklyn acted in a lawsuit","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"brought by plaintiffs","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"including a group of states","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"led by New York .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"Activists and DACA recipients march up Broadway during the start of their 'Walk","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"to Stay Home , ' a five-day 250-mile walk from New York to Washington D.C. ,","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"to demand","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"that Congress pass a Clean Dream Act , in Manhattan , New York , U.S. , February 15 , 2018 .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"/Shannon Stapleton","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"Judges Alsup and Garaufis did not say","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"that the administration could not at some point end the program ,","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"only that there was evidence","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"it did not follow the correct procedures","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"in doing so .","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"The rulings allow those","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"who had previously applied for protections","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"and whose two-year status was soon to expire","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"to apply beyond the deadline","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"set by the administration in September .","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"The original plan","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"put on hold by the court rulings","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"said","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"that only those","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"who re-applied by October","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"and whose status was due to expire by March 5","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"could re-apply .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":257,"left":0,"right":256,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":256,"left":220,"right":255,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":211,"right":219,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":186,"right":210,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":167,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"left":145,"right":166,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":140,"right":144,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":132,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":1,"right":131,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":1